  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed rear extension, as shown on the submitted plans, requires the prior approval of the local planning authority, in accordance with the requirements of Class A of Part 1 of Schedule 2 to the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended). Prior approval therefore is not granted as the submitted plans fail to show that the proposed materials used in any exterior work would be of a similar appearance to those used in the construction of the exterior of the existing dwellinghouse.",
    "The submitted information fails to demonstrate that the proposed rear extension would not result in an unacceptable loss of light impacts on the adjoining properties. The application therefore does not comply with A.3(a) A.4(3) and A.4(7) of Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended)."
